This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on April 3, 2012. It states that the President has determined it is important to the national interest to provide assistance under the Migration and Refugee Assistance Act. The assistance will not exceed $26 million from the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund and will be used to address unexpected and urgent refugee and migration needs resulting from the conflict in South Kordofan and Blue Nile States of Sudan. The memorandum authorizes the Secretary of State to publish it in the Federal Register.